'''John McAdams''' (May 3, 1941 &ndash; June 16, 2005) [[public address]] announcer for [[Philadelphia Big 5]] college basketball at the [[Palestra]] from the 1981-82 season to the 2004-05 season. He also did public address for Wilmington, DE Blue Rocks minor league baseball (Class A Kansas City Royals). Known for his smooth, easy delivery. He was the PA Announcer for the Duke-Kentucky NCAA East Region Final in 1992 at the Spectrum when Duke's Christian Laettner beat Kentucky with his famous buzzer-beater jump shot. He was also the PA announcer for the [[2005 NCAA Division I Men's Lacrosse Championship]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2009/02/14/AR2009021401356_pf.html|title=Hoops Heaven at the Palestra|date=2009-02-15|work=Washington Post|page=D09|accessdate=2009-05-25|archivedate=2009-05-23|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/5h2GQAWPx}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://media.www.dailypennsylvanian.com/media/storage/paper882/news/2000/03/07/Resources/Perspective.Time.Stands.Still.At.The.Palestra-2163086.shtml|title=Perspective: Time stands still at the Palestra|last=Moskowitz |first=Eric|date=2000-03-07|work=The Daily Pennsylvanian|accessdate=2009-05-25|archivedate=2009-05-25|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/5h2GunFk6}}</ref>

McAdams was inducted in Philadelphia Big 5 Hall of Fame in 2007.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.philadelphiabig5.org/hallfame/pbg5-hallfame.html|title=Hall of Fame - Philadelphia Big 5 Athletics|work=philadelphiabig5.org|publisher=CBS Interactive|accessdate=2009-05-25|archivedate=2009-05-25|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/5h2HBaGkP}}</ref>

